DSMC is a parallel Direct Simulation Monte Carlo code designed to run
efficiently on parallel computers.  It was developed at Sandia
National Laboratories, a US Department of Energy facility, with
funding from the DOE.  It is an open-source code, distributed freely
under the terms of the GNU Public License (GPL).

The primary authors of the code are Steve Plimpton and Michael Gallis,
who can be emailed at sjplimp@sandia.gov and magalli@sandia.gov.  The
DSMC WWW Site at www.sandia.gov/~sjplimp/dsmc.html has more
information about the code and its uses.

The DSMC distribution includes the following files and directories:

README			   this file
LICENSE			   the GNU General Public License (GPL)
bench			   benchmark problems
doc			   documentation
examples		   simple test problems
python			   Python wrapper on DSMC as a library
src			   source files
tools			   pre- and post-processing tools

Point your browser at any of these files to get started:

doc/Manual.html	           the DSMC manual
doc/Section_intro.html	   hi-level introduction to DSMC
doc/Section_start.html	   how to build and use DSMC
doc/Developer.pdf          DSMC developer guide
